<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Lee reports that the negotiations for the delimitation of Panama,
                            Colon, and the canal zone have been completed, that maps <pb facs="0673" n="585" xml:id="pg_585"/> were made, and that General Davis, the
                            minister for foreign affairs, and the attorney-general of Panama signed
                            the papers on the 16th instant.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>